{"word":"δίεμαι","slug":"δίεμαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δίεμαι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>as if from an <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a> <el>δίημι  δίω</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to flee, speed</i>, <el>πεδίοιο</el> over the plain, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>δίεσθαι</el> <i>to hasten away</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to fear</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}